{"lemma":"نُسَخُ","slug":"نُسَخُ","root":"ن.س.خ","root_slug":"ن-س-خ","root_link":"/words/roots/ن-س-خ","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":5},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n39727"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%86%D9%8F%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"copy"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"transcript"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"original, manuscript, proof sheet, impression"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"prescription, recipe"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"written amulet"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Hebrew נֻסָּח (nussɔḥ, nusákh)."},"ipa":["/nus.xa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n39727","headword_ar":"نَسَخَ","root":"nsx","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (L, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasoxN","text_ar":"نَسْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Antsx","text_ar":"انتسخ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (L;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, annulled, superseded, obliterated, effaced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cancelled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K,) a thing,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bi$aYo'K A=xara","text_ar":"بِشَىْءٍ ا=خَرَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by another thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It annulled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superseded,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and took the place of"},{"kind":"text","text":"it. (L.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxati Al$~amosu AlZ~ila","text_ar":"نَسَخَتِ الشَّمْسُ الظِّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Antsxth","text_ar":"انتسخته","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sun annulled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superseded, the shade,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and took the place of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxa","text_ar":"نَسَخَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ayobu Al$~abaAba","text_ar":"الشَّيْبُ الشَّبَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Hoariness took the place of youth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, Msb.) Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxa","text_ar":"نَسَخَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He annulled, superseded, abolished,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"made void,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substituting for it another thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxa","text_ar":"نَسَخَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A=yapF","text_ar":"ا=يَةً"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abrogated, annulled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"superseded, the verse"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the Kur-án, (Lth, Fr, S, L,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"substituting for it another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, Fr, L;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA@loA=yapi","text_ar":"بِا@لْا=يَةِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by the"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. another]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"verse:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he changed it by substituting for it another:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxa","text_ar":"نَسَخَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he changed"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by substituting for it another thing."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, L.) [See also 4.] Legal"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasox","text_ar":"نَسْخ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or abrogation, may respect the letter and the force of command, or one of these; whether the command have been performed, as is generally the case, or have not been performed, as in the case of the sacrifice of Ishmael, [or, as some of the Muslims say, agreeably with the Bible narrative, Isaac,] for Abraham was commanded to sacrifice him, and then the command was abrogated before its execution. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  Also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxa","text_ar":"نَسَخَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing. (K.) Ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxati Alr~iyHu A=vaAra Ald~aAri","text_ar":"نَسَخَتِ الرِّيحُ ا=ثَارَ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wind changed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"altered,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or, it may also be rendered,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obliterated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"effaced,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the traces of the dwelling."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxahu","text_ar":"نَسَخَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He transformed him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"metamorphosed him, into a worse,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more ugly, shape; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaxahu","text_ar":"مَسَخَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) ex."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxahu A@ll~`hu qirodFA","text_ar":"نَسَخَهُ ا@للّٰهُ قِرْدًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"God transformed him into an ape."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, Aboo-Sa'eed.) ―         -b4-  [Also, as used in post-classical, and perhaps in classical, times,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(God)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused his soul to pass into the body of another man."},{"kind":"text","text":"] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"connexion of the soul of a human being, after its departure from the body, with the body of another human being,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasoxN","text_ar":"نَسْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; with the body of"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2789},{"kind":"text","text":"a beast,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masoxN","text_ar":"مَسْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; with a plant,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fasoxN","text_ar":"فَسْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and with an inanimate and not-increasing body,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasoxN","text_ar":"رَسْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Marginal note in a copy of the KT.) [But see 1 (last sentence) in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fsx","text_ar":"فسخ"},{"kind":"text","text":". See also 6.] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxa","text_ar":"نَسَخَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He transferred"},{"kind":"text","text":"a thing"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from one place to another,"},{"kind":"text","text":"it remaining the same: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he transferred"},{"kind":"text","text":"what was in a bee-hive"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to another"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hive"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasaxa AlkitaAba","text_ar":"نَسَخَ الكِتَابَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasoxN","text_ar":"نَسْخٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Antsxhu","text_ar":"انتسخهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Msb, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Astnsxhu","text_ar":"استنسخهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) are syn., (S,) signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He copied,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transcribed, the writing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"book,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"letter for letter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA nasaxahu waA_in~amaA masaxahu","text_ar":"مَا نَسَخَهُ وَاـِنَّمَا مَسَخَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not copied it, but only corrupted it by changing the diacritical points and altering the meanings"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b8-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nasotanosixu","text_ar":"نَسْتَنْسِخُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in the Kur, xlv. 28, signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We set down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"register, and preserve:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Jel:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"We command to be transcribed and to be set down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"registered."},{"kind":"text","text":"(T.)"}],"source_refs":["L","K","S","God","Lth","Fr","TA","Msb","T","Jel"]}]}}